main event: A CIRVIS report of a satellite observed at 42°53' N 173°47' W on 15 April 1962.
interesting points: The object was reported to be moving very fast in an east-west direction,It was evaluated and suggested that it could be a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical object,The report was part of an incoming message from the Department of the Air Force,Other possible causes for evaluation were listed as unknown, There were no photographs included in the file.
witness description: A military report documenting the sighting.
